=== Confidence heuristic calibration (known limitation, not chased further) ===

LandingPadDetector's confidence is min(1, marker_area_px /
(frame_area_px * CONFIDENT_AREA_FRACTION)), CONFIDENT_AREA_FRACTION=0.15.
Camera: horizontal_fov=1.74 rad, 1280x960, marker 0.5m. At a 5m hover,
ground coverage is ~11.9m wide, so the marker subtends roughly
0.24% of frame area -- confidence ~0.016 with the current constant, far
below both MissionManager's 0.80 APPROACH_TARGET threshold and (this run
showed) unstable in the 0.50-0.70 band during closer-range descent.
CONFIDENT_AREA_FRACTION was calibrated against the wrong intuition (a
close-up, filled-frame marker) rather than this camera's actual wide FOV
and the marker's true angular size at typical operating altitude.
Flagged as follow-up, not fixed in this session: recalibrate against the
real geometry above (roughly 0.003 gets a 5m hover near the 0.80
threshold) and/or add hysteresis/smoothing to the confidence signal so
brief dips don't accumulate toward SafetyGate's fixed 5-rejection abort
during a real descent.

=== Known limitation carried over from Phase 4 (unchanged) ===

offboard_controller keeps publishing the OffboardControlMode heartbeat
after commanding AUTO_LAND, which still appears to delay PX4's
disarm-after-landing logic (vehicle stayed ARMED, nav_state AUTO_LAND,
for several minutes after touchdown in this run too) -- not fixed here,
same follow-up item as Phase 2/3/4.
